declarations.description: Represents a base element in the FHIR data model. This is the class to extend when creating components.
declarations.name: BaseElement

members.name: validate
members.description:
validate data to find complex errors not covered by primitive types. Errors can be accessed through `this.errors`.
it is recommended to call
`super.validate(T)` as well.

members.name: decorate
members.description: Override to extend the given data with some useful context

members.name: isPrepared
members.description: This method is used to indicate that the data is ready.

members.name: willRender

parameters.description: The configuration for displaying the component.
parameters.name: config

parameters.description: The extended data to be rendered, or null if none.
parameters.name: data

parameters.description: The Lit changed properties passed during `.willUpdate(changes)`
parameters.name: changes

members.description: Determines if the component will render based on the given parameters.

members.name: renderDisplay
members.description:
convenience method implemented by fhir model elements and resources. Internal and abstract classes should
contribute templateGenerators instead.

members.name: renderStructure
members.description:
Convenience method implemented by fhir model elements and resources. Internal and abstract classes should
contribute templateGenerators instead.

members.name: hasRendered

parameters.description:
The Lit changed properties passed during `.updated(changes)` which is
called after `.render()`
parameters.name: haveChanged

members.description: Called after the component has rendered.

members.name: renderEditableDisplay
members.description: Override this method to provide an alternate template when rendering editable display

members.name: renderDebug
members.description: Render formatted JSON data for debugging purposes

members.name: key
members.description: The key the element is known as in its parent data structure

members.name: data
members.description: Element data

members.name: extendedData
members.description:
The extendedData variable is used to store additional data of type T and an empty object type {}.
It can also hold a null value.

members.name: errors
members.description: An array of objects representing validation errors.

members.name: profile
members.description:
Represents the structure definition of a generic type `T` or is undefined.

This variable is used to define the structure of a type, allowing for type validation
or enforcement. It may be undefined if no structure is provided or applicable.

members.name: type
members.description: MyString

members.name: edited

parameters.name: data
parameters.description: contained data structure that can be edited

members.description:
This method is called on every PrimitiveInputEvent captured from children elements. Modify the data object
at the corresponding key with the new value in the provided data structure.

Do any other side effects required by overriding this method.

The base implementation assigns values to the contained data object. If the key does not exist then the
corresponding key is added.

members.name: mode
members.description:
Retrieves the current display mode.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: showerror
members.description:
Determines whether error messages should be displayed.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: input
members.description:
Display primitive as an input field.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: verbose
members.description:
This property determines whether verbose mode is enabled.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: summaryonly
members.description:
Only display value if the priitive also has the summary attribute

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: open
members.description:
Display the content of the component in an open state

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: getDisplayConfig
members.deprecated:
don't use this directly. Prefer config provided by method
todo: make this method private

declarations.name: when

parameters.name: target
parameters.description: The target to evaluate the evaluations against.

declarations.description:
A function that passes a target value to an array of evaluating WHEN evaluations and returns the first corresponding
THEN

```js
const year = 2022

const color = when(year,
    [2022, () => 'green'],
    [year => year > 2022, 'red'],
    otherwise('blue')
)

console.log(color) // green

```

declarations.name: NoDataObject
declarations.description:
The NoDataSet variable is a constant value of type FhirElementData.
It represents a null value for FHIR objects in the context of the Beacon system.

The NoDataSet value is created by freezing an object with a single property 'id',
which is set to the string value 'FHIR::BEACON::NULL::OBJECT'.

The NoDataSet value is immutable and cannot be modified once created.
It can be used to indicate the absence or unavailability of valid FHIR data. It is meant to be used as a default
value to differentiate between default emptiness and user-set emptiness.

declarations.name: DataContextConsumerController

declarations.description:
The DisplayContextConsumerController class is responsible for handling the display configuration context
for a given host element. It subscribes to changes in the displayConfigContext and updates the host element
accordingly.

This class implements the ReactiveController interface and can be added to a host element using the addController
method.

members.name: renderDisplay
members.description:
convenience method implemented by fhir model elements and resources. Internal and abstract classes should
contribute templateGenerators instead.

members.name: renderStructure
members.description:
Convenience method implemented by fhir model elements and resources. Internal and abstract classes should
contribute templateGenerators instead.

members.name: validate
members.description:
validate data to find complex errors not covered by primitive types. Errors can be accessed through `this.errors`.
it is recommended to call
`super.validate(T)` as well.

members.name: decorate
members.description: Override to extend the given data with some useful context

members.name: isPrepared
members.description: This method is used to indicate that the data is ready.

members.name: willRender

parameters.description: The configuration for displaying the component.
parameters.name: config

parameters.description: The extended data to be rendered, or null if none.
parameters.name: data

parameters.description: The Lit changed properties passed during `.willUpdate(changes)`
parameters.name: changes

members.description: Determines if the component will render based on the given parameters.

members.name: hasRendered

parameters.description:
The Lit changed properties passed during `.updated(changes)` which is
called after `.render()`
parameters.name: haveChanged

members.description: Called after the component has rendered.

members.name: renderEditableDisplay
members.description: Override this method to provide an alternate template when rendering editable display

members.name: renderDebug
members.description: Render formatted JSON data for debugging purposes

members.name: key
members.description: The key the element is known as in its parent data structure

members.name: data
members.description: Element data

members.name: extendedData
members.description:
The extendedData variable is used to store additional data of type T and an empty object type {}.
It can also hold a null value.

members.name: errors
members.description: An array of objects representing validation errors.

members.name: profile
members.description:
Represents the structure definition of a generic type `T` or is undefined.

This variable is used to define the structure of a type, allowing for type validation
or enforcement. It may be undefined if no structure is provided or applicable.

members.name: type
members.description: MyString

members.name: edited

parameters.name: data
parameters.description: contained data structure that can be edited

members.description:
This method is called on every PrimitiveInputEvent captured from children elements. Modify the data object
at the corresponding key with the new value in the provided data structure.

Do any other side effects required by overriding this method.

The base implementation assigns values to the contained data object. If the key does not exist then the
corresponding key is added.

members.name: mode
members.description:
Retrieves the current display mode.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: showerror
members.description:
Determines whether error messages should be displayed.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: input
members.description:
Display primitive as an input field.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: verbose
members.description:
This property determines whether verbose mode is enabled.

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: summaryonly
members.description:
Only display value if the priitive also has the summary attribute

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.name: open
members.description:
Display the content of the component in an open state

Setting the attribute overrides context-provided property.

members.deprecated:
don't use this directly. Prefer config provided by method

declarations.name: toDecimal
declarations.default: function (decimal: unknown) { if (!decimal) throw new TypeError(`decimal must be a valid number: ${decimal}`) if (!regex.test(decimal + '')) throw new TypeError(`decimal must be a valid number: ${decimal}`) if (isNaN(Number.parseFloat(decimal + ''))) throw new TypeError(`decimal must be a valid number: ${decimal}`) // Split the number into base and exponent const parts = String(decimal).split(/[eE]/) const basePart = parts[0] const exponentPart = parts[1] ? parseInt(parts[1], 10) : 0 // Remove potential leading negative sign and decimal point const baseDigits = basePart.replace(/^-|\./g, '') // Calculate the total number of digits considering the exponent const totalDigits = baseDigits.length + (exponentPart !== 0 ? Math.abs(exponentPart) : 0) if (totalDigits <= 18) { return decimal as Decimal // return decimal } throw new TypeError(`decimal must be a valid number: ${decimal}`) }

parameters.name:
{
                          key,
                          pluralBase,
                          collection,
                          generator,
                          summary = true,
                          config
                        }

parameters.description: The key to use for generating labels.
parameters.name: key

parameters.description: The base string to pluralize for the label of the wrapper.
parameters.name: pluralBase

parameters.description: The collection of items to wrap.

parameters.description: The function to generate the content of each item in the wrapper.
parameters.name: generator

parameters.description: Whether to display a summary or detailed view of the items in the wrapper.
parameters.name: summary

declarations.description: Wraps a collection of items with a `<fhir-wrapper>` component.

declarations.name: wrapLines

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key to be used for wrapping lines. It will be converted to lower case.

parameters.name: label
parameters.description: The base string to be used for pluralization.

parameters.name: collection
parameters.description: The array of strings to be processed.

parameters.name: verbose
parameters.description: A boolean value indicating whether the verbose mode is enabled or not.

parameters.name: generator

type.text: { (data: T, label: string, key: string): TemplateResult }

parameters.description: A function to generate a TemplateResult based on the provided data, label, and key.

parameters.name: summary
parameters.description: An optional boolean value indicating whether to display the summary or not.

declarations.description: Wraps lines based on the given parameters.
